cold storage and may take up to 2 minutes to export.</p>",creating:"Creating project file for {projectName}.",created:"Project export complete. You can now download {projectName}.",errorMessage:"Sorry, something went wrong while exporting your project. Please retry exporting."},jupyterInBeta:{title:"New Jupyter Project",details:"Jupyter projects are currently in beta. To create Jupyter projects here, please contact the account owner for this space and ask them to <betaHowToLink>enable the Jupyter projects beta feature</betaHowToLink> for their account.",cantAccessBetaFeatures:"Jupyter projects are currently in beta and are not available in Cloud Free or Cloud Student accounts. If you would like to create Jupyter projects in this space, you will need to first <upgradeLink>upgrade your account</upgradeLink>.",enable:{details:"Jupyter projects are currently a beta feature. Would you like to enable this feature for your account?",limitations:"Beta features have some limitations. Please the <guideLink>Posit Cloud Guide</guideLink> for more information.",submit:"Enable & Create Project"}},leaveSpace:{title:"Leave Space",info:{onlyOption:"You are about to leave {spaceName}. You will lose access to all content in this space.",options:"You are about to leave {spaceName}. What would you like to do with any content you have created in this space?"},projects:{leave:"Leave the content where it is",move:"Move content to my personal space (Your Workspace)"}},limitReached:{account_compute_hours_soft_max:{details:{anyone:{action:"To open content in this account before the next usage period, notify the account owner {ownerName} to upgrade the account.",summary:"This account has reached its compute hours limit for the current period. No content in the account can be opened until the account's next usage period begins."},owner:{action:{support:"To continue working with content, please contact technical support.",upgrade:"To continue working with content, upgrade your account."},summary:"Your account has exceeded its compute hours limit. You are unable to open content in spaces owned by your account until your next usage period begins {endDate} at {endTime}."}}},account_output_max:{details:{anyone:{action:"Archive or trash existing outputs to make room for additional outputs, or notify the account owner {ownerName} to upgrade the account.",summary:"This account has reached its limit for outputs."},owner:{action:{support:"Archive or trash existing outputs to make room for additional outputs. If you need more capacity in this space, please contact technical support.",upgrade:"Archive or trash existing outputs to make room for additional outputs. If you need more capacity in this space, please upgrade your account."},summary:"You have reached the limit for outputs in your account."}}},account_private_space_max:{details:{anyone:{action:"Archive or delete existing spaces in the account to make room for additional spaces, or notify the account owner {ownerName} to upgrade the account.",summary:"This account has reached its limit for creating spaces."},owner:{action:{support:"To create additional spaces, please contact technical support.",upgrade:"To create additional spaces, upgrade your account."},summary:"You have reached the limit for creating spaces in your account."}},multiOwner:"This account has reached its limit for creating spaces. You can select a different account ... or upgrade this account."},account_project_max:{details:{anyone:{action:"Archive or trash existing projects to make room for additional projects, or notify the account owner {ownerName} to upgrade the account.",summary:"This account has reached its limit for creating projects."},owner:{action:{support:"Archive or trash existing projects to make room for additional projects. If you need more capacity in this space, please contact technical support.",upgrade:"Archive or trash existing projects to make room for additional projects. If you need more capacity in this space, please upgrade your account."},summary:"You have reached the limit for creating projects in your account."}}},account_require_paid_participants_flag:{details:{owner:{action:{upgrade:"Please upgrade your Cloud account to one of our paid plans."},summary:"You must have a paid subscription to work with content in this space."}}},account_suspension:{details:{anyone:{action:"Contact the account owner {ownerName} to proceed.",summary:"Your account is suspended until {suspendedUntil}."},owner:{action:{support:"If you believe this to be in error, please contact technical support.",upgrade:"To continue using projects, upgrade your account."},summary:'Your account is suspended until {suspendedUntil} due to "{suspendedReason}".'}}},space_content_max:{details:{anyone:{action:"Archive or trash existing content to make room for additional content, or notify the account owner {ownerName} to upgrade the account.",summary:"This space has reached its limit for creating content."},owner:{action:{support:"Archive or trash existing content to make room for additional content. If you need more capacity in this space, please contact technical support.",upgrade:"Archive or trash existing content to make room for additional content. If you need more capacity in this space, please upgrade your account."},summary:"This space has reached its limit for creating content."}},capacity:{owner:"Archive or trash existing content to make room for additional content. If you need more capacity in this space, please upgrade your account.",anyone:"Archive or trash existing content to make room for additional content, or notify the account owner {ownerName} to upgrade the account."}},space_member_max:{details:{anyone:{action:"To add additional members, notify the account owner {ownerName} to upgrade the account.",summary:"This space has reached its limit for adding members."},owner:{action:{support:"To add additional members, please contact technical support.",upgrade:"To add additional members, upgrade your account."},summary:"You have reached the limit for adding members in this space."}},capacity:{owner:"To add additional members, upgrade your account.",anyone:"To add additional members, notify the account owner {ownerName} to upgrade the account."}},space_template_max:{details:{anyone:{action:"Archive or trash existing project templates to make room for additional project templates, or notify the account owner {ownerName} to upgrade the account.",summary:"This space has reached its limit for creating project templates."},owner:{action:{support:"Archive or trash existing project templates to make room for new project templates. If you need more capacity in this space, please contact technical support.",upgrade:"Archive or trash existing project templates to make room for new project templates. If you need more capacity in this space, please upgrade your account."},summary:"You have reached the limit for creating project templates in this space."}}},temporaryCopy:{purpose:"Warning",account:{details:{anyone:{action:"To save a permanent copy of this project, archive or trash existing projects, or notify the account owner {ownerName} to upgrade the account.",summary:"This account has reached its limit for creating projects. You are opening a temporary copy, but you will not be able to save any changes you make."},owner:{action:{support:"If you would like to save a permanent copy of this project, please contact technical support.",upgrade:"If you would like to save a permanent copy of this project, upgrade your account."},summary:"You have reached the limit for creating projects in your account. You are opening a temporary copy, but you will not be able to save any changes you make."}}},space:{details:{anyone:{action:"To save a permanent copy of this project, archive or trash existing content, or notify the account owner {ownerName} to upgrade the account.",summary:"This space has reached its limit for creating content. You are opening a temporary copy, but you will not be able to save any changes you make."},owner:{action:{support:"If you would like to save a permanent copy of this project, please contact technical support.",upgrade:"If you would like to save a permanent copy of this project, upgrade your account."},summary:"You have reached the limit for creating content in this space. You are opening a temporary copy, but you will not be able to save any changes you make."}}}},default:{details:{anyone:{action:"To continue, notify the account owner {ownerName} to upgrade the account.",summary:"This account has reached its limit for this operation."},owner:{action:{support:"To continue, please contact technical support.",upgrade:"To continue, upgrade your account."},summary:"Your account has reached the limit for this operation."}},purpose:"Limit Reached"}},manageCustomList:{visibility:{label:"Who can view this list",private:"Just admins and moderators in {spaceName}",public:"Everyone in {spaceName}"},errors:{name:"Enter a name",notFound:"Unable to save changes since the list has been deleted. Please refresh the page."},info:{label:"More info about list access",general:"This setting controls who can view the list; access to particular content in the list is determined by that content's access setting.",modify:"Access to a list can be changed at anytime via List / Settings."},title:{add:"New List",modify:"List Settings"}},moveContent:{title:"Move Content",cannotMoveFromSelectedSpaceAccount:{individual:"You can move content into {selectedSpaceName}, but you cannot move it back out. {ownerName} could grant you that permission in the future.",org:"You can move content into {selectedSpaceName}, but you cannot move it back out. An admin of {ownerName} could grant you that permission in the future."},cannotMoveFromCurrentSpaceAccount:{individual:"{selectedSpaceName} is in another account and you do not have permission to move the content out of the current account. Contact {ownerName} to request permission.",org:"{selectedSpaceName} is in another account and you do not have permission to move the content out of the current account. Contact an admin of {ownerName} to request permission."},details:"Select a new space for {content}",info:{description:"If {author} does not have access to the space you select, they will no longer have access to the content.",label:"More info about accessing moved content"}},newGitProject:{title:"New Project from Git Repository",projectType:"Project type",repoURL:"URL of your Git Repository",repoURLError:"A URL is required",repoInfo:{description:'<p><strong>GitHub Repositories</strong></p><p>You can access either private or public GitHub repositories. To access private repositories, you will first need to enable GitHub private repository access in <a href="{userAuthenticationLink}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Posit User Settings</a>.</p><p><strong>Other Repositories</strong></p><p>With this feature, you can only access other repositories that are public.<p><p>To access a private repository, you must clone the repository yourself. Refer to the <a href="https://docs.posit.co/cloud/guide/advanced/#working-with-private-git-projects" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Working with Private, Non-GitHub Projects</a> section of the Guide for details.</p>',label:"More info about GitHub repositories"},friendlyErrorTitle:"Unable To Create Project from GitHub Repository",friendlyErrorMessage:"Sorry, something went wrong while creating your project. Please check the URL.",includePackages:"Packages",includePackagesInfo:{description:"This space has a base project for new projects. You can include its packages in the new project we'll create from your Git repository.",label:"More info about included packages"},includePackagesLabel:"Add packages from the base project",gitHubRepoErrorTitle:"Cannot access git repository",repoURLAccessError:"<div><p>We are unable to access a repository at that URL - make sure you entered the URL correctly and that the repository is accessible to your currently linked GitHub account.<p></div>",badGitHubURL:"<div><p>We are unable to access a repository at that URL - make sure you entered the URL correctly.<p></div>",badURL:'<div><p>We can’t access the repository for the URL provided. If you’re trying to access a private GitHub repository, you will first need to enable GitHub private repository access in <a href="{userAuthenticationLink}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Posit User Settings</a>.<p></div>',privateRepoError:'<div><p>We are unable to access a repository at that URL, make sure you entered the URL correctly. If it is a private repository, you must first enable GitHub private repository access in <a href="{userAuthenticationLink}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Posit User Settings</a>.<p></div>',rstudioProject:"RStudio Project",jupyterProject:"Jupyter Project",jupyterInfo:"<p>This feature is not yet enabled for Jupyter projects.</p><p>However, you can clone a git repo into a Jupyter project by doing the following.</p><ul><li>Create a Jupyter project via the New Project menu</li><li>In the project, open a new terminal and type <code>git clone <em>your-git-repo-url</em></code></li></ul>"},newProjectFromTemplate:{filterTitle:{ide:"RStudio Project Templates",jupyter:"Jupyter Project Templates"},noTemplatesFound:"No matching templates found.",noTemplatesInSpace:"No templates are available from {spaceName}. See the {link} section of the Guide for how to create custom templates to streamline your workflows.",spaceTitle:"From: {spaceName}",template:{access:"Access: {access}",from:"From: {from}",type:"Type: {type}",updated:"Updated: {updated}"},title:"New Project from Template"},outputChangeResourcesRenderInProgress:{title:"Change Resources",details:"A job to generate a new revision of this output is already progress, and the resource settings for the job cannot be changed until it has finished. See History for revision build information."},outputRefreshRenderInProgress:{title:"Refresh Output",details:"A job to generate a new revision of this output is already progress, and this output cannot be refreshed again until that job has finished. See History for revision build information."},reactivateSubscription:{title:"Reactivate {name}",description:"<p>Your subscription was canceled on {canceled_at} and your account will revert to Cloud Free on {cycle_end}.</p><p>Would you like to reactivate your {name} subscription?</p>"},relaunchProject:{title:"Relaunch Project",areYouSure:{ide:"<p>We recommend doing this only if your project is not loading or is completely unresponsive.</p><p>This will close and reopen your project in a new session. You may lose the console history, any data saved in the R environment, and any unsaved changes to files.</p><p>Relaunch {projectName}?</p>",jupyter:"<p>We recommend doing this only if your project is not loading or is completely unresponsive.</p><p>This will close and reopen your project in a new session. You will lose the terminal history, any variables saved in running notebooks, and any unsaved changes to files.</p><p>Relaunch {projectName}?</p>"}},removeAccountMember:{actions:{archive:"Move content to its respective spaces' archive",leave:"Leave the content where it is",trash:"Move content to its respective spaces' trash"},info:{leave:{noActions:"Are you sure you want to leave this account? You will lose access to all spaces and content in {accountName}."},remove:{actions:"You are about to remove {username}. They will also be removed from any spaces belonging to this account. What would you like to do with any content they have created?",noActions:"Are you sure you want to remove {username} from this account? They will also be removed from any spaces belonging to this account."}},title:{leave:"Leave Account",remove:"Remove Member"}},removeMember:{title:"Remove Member",info:{options:"You are about to remove {username}. What would you like to do with any content they have created in this space?"},projects:{archive:"Move content to the archive",leave:"Leave the content where it is",move:'Move content to their personal space (titled "Your Workspace")',trash:"Move content to the trash"}},requestBetaFeature:{collabEditing:{description:"Collaborative editing is a beta feature that allows multiple users to simultaneously edit the same project.",enable:"Enable Collaborative Editing?",warning:"This feature has <betaDocsLink>known limitations</betaDocsLink>, including a potential for data loss, that should be taken into consideration before enabling it."},jupyter:{description:"Jupyter projects is a beta feature that allows you to create Jupyter notebooks in Posit Cloud.",enable:"Enable Jupyter Projects?",title:"Jupyter Projects",warning:"This feature has <betaDocsLink>known limitations</betaDocsLink> that should be taken into consideration before enabling it."}},requestQuote:{title:"Contact Our Sales Team",first:"First name",last:"Last name",email:"Email",notes:"Message / Questions",policy:'I accept the Posit <a href="https://posit.co/about/privacy-policy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy policy</a>',contact:"You should hear back from us within 2 business days.",pending:"Sending your request",success:"Thank you! Your request has been sent. You’ll hear back from us soon.",org:{info:"Thanks for your interest in a Cloud Organization plan. Please supply the following information and we'll get right back to you.",organization:"Organization / School",role:"Your role",users:"Approximate number of users"}},restoreSpace:{details:{membership:"You will be added to the space as an admin, and will be its only member.",result:"The space and all its content will be un-archived."},title:"Restore Space"},selectContentImage:{image:{alt:{bars:"bar graph",circles:"circles",default:"default",grid:"grid",hexes:"hexes",lines:"line graph",splatter:"splatter",triangles:"triangles"}},title:"Select Image"},shareContentLink:{title:"Share Link",selectMembers:"Space members to send the link to",selectAdminsModerators:"Space admins and moderators to send the link to",email:"Email address to send the link to",message:"Message",send:"Send",disclaimer:"Currently, only you can access this content. Before you can share a link to it, go to the Access panel in Settings and change who can view the content to “Everyone”.",info:{description:"Sharing a link to your content does NOT confer access to the content - it just emails a link. Access is controlled via the Access panel in Settings.",label:"More info about content access"},errorNoMemberPicked:"Select a member",errorNoEmail:"Enter an email address",linkSent:"Link Sent"},transferAccount:{title:"Change Owner",fields:{newOwner:{title:"New Owner Email"}}},trashContent:{title:"Move to Trash",details:"Are you sure you want to move {name} to the trash?"},upgradeProjectOS:{title:"Project Requires Upgrade",info:"<p>This project is currently using a version of the operating system that is no longer supported.</p><p>We will upgrade it to a new version of the operating system before opening it.</p>"},userName:{title:"Name Required",details:"Your name is required to use Posit Cloud and somehow we don't seem to have one for you. Please enter your first and last names below.",firstName:"First name",lastName:"Last name",errors:{noFirstName:"Please enter your first name",noLastName:"Please enter your last name"}},viewApplicationLogs:{download:"Download Logs",project:{title:"Project Logs"},output:{title:"Output Logs"},refresh:"Refresh logs",updated:"Last updated: {when}"},viewOutputHistory:{current:"current revision",download:{log:"Download Log",source:"Download Source",sourceAria:"download revision source from {date}"},info:{title:"Build Info",status:{failed:"Failed",running:"In Progress",success:"Succeeded",title:"Status"},duration:{minutes:"{duration} minutes",seconds:"{duration} seconds",title:"Duration",tooLong:"{duration} hours"},resources:{title:"Resources",value:"{memory} GB RAM, {cpu} CPU"},versions:{python:"Python: {version}",quarto:"Quarto: {version}",R:"R: {version}",title:"Versions"}},loading:"Getting log",log:"Build Log",revisions:"Revisions",title:"History",updated:"Last updated: {when}"}},learn:{menu:{cheatsheets:"Cheatsheets",guide:"Guide",recipes:"Recipes",whatsNew:"What's New"}},guide:{bannerDescription:"Get started with Posit Cloud.",bannerTitle:"Posit Cloud Guide",advancedTopics:{externalDataSources:"External Databases"}},whatsNew:{bannerTitle:"What's New on Posit Cloud"},recipes:{banner:{description:"Some tasty R code snippets",title:"Posit Recipes"},categories:{basics:{description:"Do basic tasks with R, like import data and call functions.",recipes:{basicb1:"Arithmetic with single numbers",basicb2:"Call a function on a number",basicb3a:"Obey R's naming rules",basicb4:"Run a function",basicq3:"Create a table manually",importa1:"Read a CSV file (.csv)",importe:"Read a character-delimited file (.txt)",importf:"Read an Excel file (.xls, .xlsx)"},title:"R Basics"},datetime:{description:"Work with date-time data.",recipes:{datetimea:"Parse a string to date or datetime",datetimea1:"Parse datetimes with mixed formats",datetimea3:"Manually create a date with make_date()",datetimeb:"Extract components of dates and datetimes",datetimeb1:"Extract the day of the week from dates or date-times",datetimeb2:"Extract a month as a name or abbreviated name",datetimeb3:"Summarize data over units of time",datetimec:"Update date-times",datetimed:"Round a date or datetime",datetimee:"Display date-times in a new time zone",datetimee1:"Replace the time zone of a date-time",datetimef1:"How should I use R to represent the passage of time?",datetimef2:"Add a duration to a date-time",datetimef2a:"Create a duration",datetimef3:"Add a period of time to a datetime",datetimef3a:"Create a period",datetimeg:"Create an interval",datetimeg1:"Check if a date or time lies within an interval",datetimeg2:"Check whether two events or processes overlap",datetimeg3:"Measure the length of an interval with a specified unit of time",datetimeh:"Use dates to build customized character strings",datetimeh1:"Reformat a date as a character string"},title:"Dates & Times"},factors:{description:"Work with categorical data in R.",recipes:{factorsa:"Factor basics",factorsb:"Find the levels of a factor",factorsc:"Transform an object into a factor",factorsd:"Manually reorder factor levels",factorse:"Reorder factor levels by frequency",factorsf:"Reorder a factor by another variable",factorsh:"Reverse the levels of a factor",factorsj:"Recode individual factor levels",factorsk:"Lump infrequent levels together",factorsl:"Combine factors"},title:"Factors"},modeling:{description:"Fit basic models and work with the output.",recipes:{modelb:"Make a table of metrics related to a model’s components",modelc:"Make a table of metrics related to a model’s goodness of fit",modeld:"Make a table of metrics related to the data points used to train/fit a model",modeld1:"Make a table of model predictions given new input/test data",modele:"Perform an analysis of variance (ANOVA)",modelg1:"Build a survival object to use in survival models",modelg2:"Generate and plot a Kaplan Meier curve",modelg4:"Check for significant differences between survival curves",modelh1:"Fit a Cox proportional hazards model"},title:"Model Data"},strings:{description:"Work with character strings in R.",recipes:{stringsa:"Find the length of a string",stringsa1:"Remove unwanted whitespace from a string",stringsa2:"Pad a string",stringsa3:"String basics",stringsb:"Combine strings",stringsb1:"Collapse a vector of strings",stringsc:"Build strings from text and data",stringsd:"Remove and replace specific patterns in strings",stringse:"Extract a portion of a string",stringsf:"What are special characters?",stringsg:"Regular expressions",stringsg1:"Visualize matches in a string",stringsg2:"Write a regular expression that uses a quantifier",stringsg3:"Match a set of characters",stringsg4:"Match the start or end of a string",stringsg5:"Refer to a matched pattern within one regular expression",stringsg6:"Use look arounds to find matches",stringsh:"Determine if a string contains a pattern",stringsh1:"Extract strings that match a pattern",stringsh2:"Extract a pattern from a string",stringsh3:"Count the number of matches of a pattern in a string",stringsi:"Change the case of a string"},title:"Strings"},tables:{description:"Polish tables for display and publication.",recipes:{tablea1:"Create a table for publication",tableb1:"Format the column names of a table for publication",tabled1:"Format the title of a table for publication",tabled2:"Format footnotes in a table for publication",tabled3:"Add a label that spans several columns in a table for publication",tabled4:"Add a label above the row names in a table for publication",tablee:"Format values in a table for publication",tablef:"Add color based on cell values in a table for publication",tableg:"Format missing values in a table for publication",tableh:"Create groups of rows in a table for publication",tablei:"Add summary rows to the bottom of a table for publication",tablej:"Style cells and values in a table for publication"},title:"Figures & Tables"},transform:{description:"Do things like filter, sort, and pivot your tables of data.",recipes:{transforma:"Extract columns from a table as a new table",transformc:"Rename columns in a table",transformf:"Add a column to a table and compute its values",transformh:"Compute summary statistics for a table",transformi:"Compute summary statistics for groups of rows within a table",transforml:"Filter your table to rows with specific values",transformm:"Group a continuous variable into categories",transformo1:"Sort a table by row",transformp:"Create a two-way contingency table",transformp1:"Create a one-way frequency table",transformp2:"Create a three-way contingency table",transformu:"Pull first or last observation of each group from a table"},title:"Transform Tables"},visualize:{description:"Plot your data in various ways.",recipes:{visualizea1a:"Visualize two vectors using a scatterplot",visualizea3:"Visualize data with a scatterplot",visualizea4:"Visualize counts with a bar chart",visualizea4a:"Visualize grouped counts with a stacked bar chart",visualizea5:"Visualize a distribution with a histogram",visualizea6:"Visualize ordered continuous data with a line chart",visualizea7:"Visualize distributions with boxplots",visualizeg:"Change the axis labels of a plot"},title:"Visualize Data"}},primers:"Posit Primers have been replaced by Posit Recipes, this collection of R code snippets and instructions featuring up-to-date best practices for coding in R. Please update any bookmarks you may have!",source:{attribution:"These recipes were created by the Posit Academy team. {link}",learnMore:"Learn more about Posit Academy."}},licenseSeats:{add:{billing:{summary:{plural:"You will be billed immediately for the remaining days in your current usage period for the additional {seatDiff} seats.",singular:"You will be billed immediately for the remaining days in your current usage period for the additional seat."}},hours:"An additional {hours} compute hours per month will be included with your plan.",instructor:{summary:{plural:"You are subscribing for an additional {seatDiff} seats @ {seatPrice} / instructor / month.",singular:"You are subscribing for an additional seat @ {seatPrice} / instructor / month."}},member:{summary:{plural:"You are subscribing for an additional {seatDiff} seats @ {seatPrice} / member / month.",singular:"You are subscribing for an additional seat @ {seatPrice} / member / month."}},student:{summary:{plural:"You are subscribing for an additional {seatDiff} seats @ {seatPrice} / student / month.",singular:"You are subscribing for an additional seat @ {seatPrice} / student / month."}}},billing:{additional:"You will be billed immediately for the days remaining in your current usage period for the additional cost.",newPrice:"You will then be billed monthly as follows:",reduced:"We will credit your account for the days remaining in your current usage period for the reduced cost.",same:"Your monthly bill will remain the same."},current:{instructor:"You currently have {max} instructor seat(s) - how many do you want in total?",member:"You currently have {max} member seat(s) - how many do you want in total?",student:"You currently have {max} student seat(s) - how many do you want in total?"},remove:{billing:{summary:{plural:"We will credit your account for the days remaining in your current usage period for the {seatDiff} removed seats.",singular:"We will credit your account for the days remaining in your current usage period for the removed seat."}},both:{tooFew:"You currently have {currentMemberCount} active instructors and {currentStudentCount} active students in your account."},hours:"{hours} fewer compute hours per month will be included with your plan.",instructor:{summary:{plural:"You are subscribing for {seatDiff} fewer seats @ {seatPrice} / instructor / month.",singular:"You are subscribing for one fewer seat @ {seatPrice} / instructor / month."},resolution:{plural:"To reduce your instructor seat count to {newMemberCount}, you must first remove {removeCount} instructors.",singular:"To reduce your instructor seat count to {newMemberCount}, you must first remove 1 instructor."},tooFew:"You currently have {currentMemberCount} active instructors in your account."},link:"Use the {link} page to remove account members.",member:{summary:{plural:"You are subscribing for {seatDiff} fewer seats @ {seatPrice} / member / month.",singular:"You are subscribing for one fewer seat @ {seatPrice} / member / month."},resolution:{plural:"To reduce your member seat count to {newMemberCount}, you must first remove {removeCount} account members.",singular:"To reduce your member seat count to {newMemberCount}, you must first remove 1 account member."},tooFew:"You currently have {currentMemberCount} active members in your account."},student:{summary:{plural:"You are subscribing for {seatDiff} fewer seats @ {seatPrice} / student / month.",singular:"You are subscribing for one fewer seat @ {seatPrice} / student / month."},resolution:{plural:"To reduce your student seat count to {newStudentCount}, you must first remove {removeCount} students.",singular:"To reduce your student seat count to {newStudentCount}, you must first remove 1 student."},tooFew:"You currently have {currentStudentCount} active students in your account."}},seatCount:{instructor:"Instructor Seat Count",member:"Member Seat Count",student:"Student Seat Count"},seats:"seats",title:"Change Seat Count",updateSubscription:"Update Subscription"},memberPicker:{noMatches:"No matches",listMore:"List more",getting:"Loading"},plansMenu:{all:"All Plans",basic:"Basic",free:"Free",instructor:"Instructor",standard:"Standard",student:"Student"},plans:{academic:{eligible:{title:"are you eligible?"},institution:{email:"Your email affiliated with the institution",name:"Your institution",role:"Your role in the institution"}},account:"Account:",actions:{change:"Change Plan",signUp:"Sign Up",subscribe:"Subscribe",requestQuote:"Request a Quote",requestOrderForm:"Request Order Form"},billing:{minAmount:"Your order must total at least {minAmount} to pay your entire bill in advance.",monthlyBillingOption:"Pay monthly and adjust or cancel at any time",payUpfrontBillingOption:"Pay the entire bill in advance for a semester or year",question:"how would you like to be billed?",title:"Billing:"},cancel:"Cancel Plan",canceled:"Canceled, effective {date}",confirmChange:"Are you sure you want to change your {currentPlan} plan to a {newPlan} plan?",cost:{rate:{amount:{metered:'<price><Amount value="{value}" /></price> / month + tax + overage fees',unmetered:'<price><Amount value="{value}" /></price> / month + tax'},breakdown:{instructor:"1 instructor @ {amount} / month",instructors:"{memberCount} instructors @ {amount} / month",member:"1 member @ {amount} / month",members:"{memberCount} members @ {amount} / month",month:{instructor:"For 1 month: 1 instructor @ {amount} / month",instructors:"For 1 month: {memberCount} instructors @ {amount} / month",member:"For 1 month: 1 member @ {amount} / month",members:"For 1 month: {memberCount} members @ {amount} / month"},months:{instructor:"For {monthCount} months: 1 instructor @ {amount} / month",instructors:"For {monthCount} months: {memberCount} instructors @ {amount} / month",member:"For {monthCount} months: 1 member @ {amount} / month",members:"For {monthCount} months: {memberCount} members @ {amount} / month"},student:" & 1 student @ {amount} / month",students:" & {studentCount} students @ {amount} / month"},fixed:'<span class="planPrice">{amount}</span> + tax',info:"More info about the cost of this plan",perpetual:'<span class="planPrice">{amount}</span> / forever',metered:'<span class="planPrice">{amount}</span> / month + tax + overage fees',unmetered:'<span class="planPrice">{amount}</span> / month + tax'},amount:'<span class="dollars">${dollars}</span><span class="cents">{cents}</span>'},currentPlan:{title:"This is your current plan.",cancellationDate:"It has been canceled, effective {endDate}."},definitions:{hours:"<strong>Compute hours</strong> represent how much time a project is open or running with a particular configuration, computed as <code>(RAM + CPUs allocated) / 2 x hours.</code> For example, working with a project for 1 hour with 2 GB of RAM and 1 CPU allocated consumes 1.5 compute hours.",cpu:"Content is deployed in its own container. You can configure the amount of computing power allocated to the container.",ram:"Content is deployed in its own container. You can configure the amount of RAM allocated to the container."},estimateBill:{computeHours:"Learn more about compute hours",instructor:{count:"Number of instructors",hours:"Average compute hours per instructor per month"},lineItem:{computeHours:"Compute hours ({overageHours} @ {overagePrice} / hour)",computeHoursCalculation:"{totalHours} estimated total compute hours - {includedHours} included with your subscription",instructor:"1 instructor @ {instructorPrice} / month",instructors:"{instructorCount} instructors @ {instructorPrice} / month",monthlyCost:"Estimated Monthly Bill",noComputeHours:"Compute hours: {totalHours} (all included)"},student:{count:"Number of students",hours:"Average compute hours per student per month"},title:"Estimate Your Monthly Bill"},faqs:{account:{existing:"<strong>For an existing account:</strong> select a {planType} plan for your existing account to change the limits for spaces and content that your account owns.",moreInfo:'For more information on account and space membership, please refer to the <a href="https://docs.posit.co/cloud/guide/accounts/#organization-accounts-and-spaces">Posit Cloud Guide</a>.',organization:"<strong>For your organization/team:</strong> select a {planType} plan for <strong>your organization/team</strong> if you want to allow others to create and manage spaces, and content across those spaces, and/or if you need to enable SSO on your account. If you select this option, we will create a <strong>new organization account</strong> for this purpose. Any existing content you wish to use will need to be moved manually, your existing account will be unchanged.",title:"Who is my subscription for?",you:"<strong>For you:</strong> select a {planType} plan for <strong>you</strong> if you will be solely responsible for creating and managing new spaces (space admins and moderators can always manage space membership once a space has been created). If you purchase a {planType} plan for yourself, it will be applied to your existing account, if you have one, and affect the limits for spaces and content that your account owns. If you do not yet have a Posit Cloud account, we will create one for you."},cancel:{answer:"You can cancel your subscription at any time - the cancellation takes effect at the end of your current usage period.",consequence:"If you do cancel, none of your work is deleted - your account is downgraded to the Cloud Free plan and subject to its time and resource limits.",question:"Can I cancel my subscription?"},instructors:{question:"Can I increase or decrease the number of instructors on my plan?",students:{question:"Can I increase or decrease the number of instructors or students on my plan?"}},members:{answer:"You can increase or decrease your account membership at any time. If you increase it, you will be charged a prorated amount for the remainder of your current month, and then billed the full price per member in subsequent months. If you decrease it, you will receive a prorated credit for the remainder of your current month, and the credit will be applied to future invoices.",question:"Can I increase or decrease the number of members on my plan?"},orderRequest:{cancel:{answer:"Please contact our support team to cancel or switch plans.",question:"Can I cancel or switch plans?"},members:{answer:"Please contact our support team to adjust the number of members on your plan.",question:"Can I increase or decrease the number of members on my plan after purchase?"},startDate:{answer:"Your plan begins on the start date you specify.",question:"When does my plan begin?"},title:"FAQs for Pay in Advance Plans"},overages:{computeHours:"See the compute hours info in the features area for more details on compute hours.",definition:{individual:"{computeHoursMax} compute hours per month are included with this plan. More than {computeHoursMax} compute hours are billed at {overagePrice} per additional compute hour.",organization:"{computeHoursMax} compute hours per member per month are included in this plan. You have currently selected {maxMembers} members for your account, giving you a pool of {totalComputeHoursMax} compute hours per month. More than {totalComputeHoursMax} compute hours are billed at {overagePrice} per additional compute hour."},question:"What are overages?",whenCharged:"Any overages are charged monthly, along with the subscription fee for the upcoming month."},startDate:{answer:"It begins when you subscribe. Your monthly usage and billing period is tied to the start date of your subscription.",question:"When does my subscription begin?"},students:{question:"Can I increase or decrease the number of students on my plan?"},switchPlans:{answer:"You can switch plans at any time. If your new plan costs more, you will be charged a prorated amount for the remainder of the current month, and then billed the full price in subsequent months. If your new plan costs less, you will receive a prorated credit for the remainder of the current month, and the credit will be applied to future invoices.",org:"If you find you need a plan for your organization/team after subscribing for yourself, you will need a separate organization account for this purpose. Please see the previous question for more information.",question:"Can I switch plans?"},taxExempt:{answer:"For your initial purchase, the invoice will reflect the tax charge if applicable depending on local and state laws. Once you have purchased a plan, please email support@posit.co and provide us with your Cloud Account ID (which can be found under your account settings in Posit Cloud), along with a valid exemption certificate, and any relevant supporting information. Once the certificate is validated, we will mark the account as tax-exempt for future charges, and process a refund for any sales tax charged initially if applicable.",question:"My organization is tax-exempt. How do I make a tax-exempt purchase?"}},features:{beta:{info:"You gain access to new features while they are still in beta and can configure which of them you would like to enable.",infoLabel:"More info about beta features",name:"Beta Features"},concurrentProjects:{detail:"This limit is enforced on a per-user basis; if this limit is exceeded, projects will go idle in the order they were opened.",explanation:{limited:"Any user can have up to {limit} projects owned by this account running simultaneously.",unlimited:"Any user can have an unlimited number of projects owned by this account running simultaneously."},infoLabel:"More info about concurrent projects",name:"Concurrent Projects",perUser:"per user"},connections:{details:{limit_one:"You can create 1 data connection per space.",limit_other:"You can create up to {count} data connections per space.",unlimited:"You can create an unlimited number of data connections per space.",value:"{spaceConnectionMax} per space"},infoLabel:"More info about data connections",limit:{many:"You can create up to {connections} data connections per space.",infinite:"You can create an unlimited number of data connections per space.",one:"You can create 1 data connection per space.",value:"{max} per space"},name:"Data Connections"},configured:"configured per project",cpu:{details:{defaults:"You can allocate up to {max} CPU per project - and allow others in your shared spaces to do the same.",overrides:"You can allocate up to {projectMax} CPU per project - and allow others in your shared spaces to do the same."},infoLabel:"More info about max CPU",jobs:"{jobMax} CPU per job",max:"{max} CPU",name:"Max CPU",outputs:"{outputMax} CPU per output",projects:"{projectMax} CPU per project"},execution:{details:{defaults:"Your projects can execute code in the background without interaction for up to {hours}.",defaults_one:"Your projects can execute code in the background without interaction for up to 1 hour.",defaults_other:"Your projects can execute code in the background without interaction for up to {count} hours.",overrides:"Your projects can execute code in the background without interaction for up to {projectHours}. Your jobs can run for up to {jobHours}.",hour:"1 hour",hours:"{max} hours"},infoLabel:"More info about max execution",jobs:"{jobHours} per job",name:"Max Execution",projects:"{projectHours} per project"},hours:{additional:"additional @ {cost} per hour",infoLabel:"More info about compute hours",name:"Compute Hours",perMonth:"included per month"},instructors:{infoLabel:"More info about instructors",limit:"You can have up to {membersLimit} instructors in your account.",name:"Instructors"},members:{infoLabel:"More info about account members",limit:"You can have up to {membersLimit} members in your account.",name:"Members"},onlineSupport:{access:"You can access our online support team directly to resolve any technical issues.",infoLabel:"More info about online support",name:"Online Support",noAccess:"This plan does not include access to our online support team to resolve technical issues."},outputs:{cpu:{limit:{many:"You can allocate up to {cpuLimit} CPUs per output - and allow others in your shared spaces to do the same.",one:"You can allocate up to {cpuLimit} CPU per output - and allow others in your shared spaces to do the same."},name:"Output Max CPU"},configured:"configured per output",description:"Outputs include apps, documents, sites, plots, and APIs.",doesNotCount:"What does not count towards your cap?",infoLabel:"More info about outputs",limit:{infinite:"There is practically no limit on the number of outputs you can publish, or that can be published in your shared spaces.",thisPlan:"This plan has a cap of {limit} outputs. When you are at the cap, you cannot publish additional outputs.",yourPlan:"Your plan has a cap of {limit} outputs. When you are at the cap, you cannot publish additional outputs."},name:"Outputs",otherSpaces:"Your outputs in others' shared spaces",ownedSpace:"Outputs in your shared space (both yours and others' outputs)",ram:{limit:{many:"You can allocate up to {gb} GBs of RAM per output - and allow others in your shared spaces to do the same.",one:"You can allocate up to {gb} GB of RAM per output - and allow others in your shared spaces to do the same."},name:"Output Max RAM"},whatCounts:"Which outputs count towards your cap?",yourWorkspace:'Outputs in "Your Workspace"'},projects:{cpu:{limit:{many:"You can allocate up to {cpuLimit} CPUs per project - and allow others in your shared spaces to do the same.",one:"You can allocate up to {cpuLimit} CPU per project - and allow others in your shared spaces to do the same."},name:"Project Max CPU"},configured:"configured per project",doesNotCount:"What does not count towards your cap?",infoLabel:"More info about projects",limit:{infinite:"There is practically no limit on the number of projects you can create, or that can be created in your shared spaces.",thisPlan:"This plan has a cap of {projectsLimit} projects. When you are at the cap, you cannot create additional projects.",yourPlan:"Your plan has a cap of {projectsLimit} projects. When you are at the cap, you cannot create additional projects."},name:"Projects",otherSpaces:"Your projects in others' shared spaces",ownedSpace:"Projects in your shared space (both yours and others' projects)",ram:{limit:{many:"You can allocate up to {gb} GBs of RAM per project - and allow others in your shared spaces to do the same.",one:"You can allocate up to {gb} GB of RAM per project - and allow others in your shared spaces to do the same."},name:"Project Max RAM"},whatCounts:"Which projects count towards your cap?",yourWorkspace:'Projects in "Your Workspace"'},projectTemplates:{details:{limit_one:"You can create 1 project template per space.",limit_other:"You can create up to {count} project templates per space.",unlimited:"You can create an unlimited number of project templates per space.",value:"{projectTemplateMax} per space"},infoLabel:"More info about project templates",limit:{infinite:"You can create an unlimited number of project templates per space.",many:"You can create up to {max} project templates per space.",one:"You can create 1 project template per space.",value:"{max} per space"},name:"Project Templates"},ram:{details:{defaults:"You can allocate up to {max} GB of RAM per project - and allow others in your shared spaces to do the same.",overrides:"You can allocate up to {projectMax} GB of RAM per project - and allow others in your shared spaces to do the same."},infoLabel:"More info about max RAM",jobs:"{jobMax} GB per job",max:"{max} GB",name:"Max RAM",outputs:"{outputMax} GB per output",projects:"{projectMax} GB per project"},spaces:{configured:"configured per space",infoLabel:"More info about shared spaces",limit_one:"You can create 1 shared space with up to {memberMax} members and {contentMax} content items in the space.",limit_other:"You can create {count} shared spaces with up to {memberMax} members and {contentMax} content items in a space.",limit:"You can create {spacesLimit} shared spaces with up to {spaceMemberLimit} members and {spaceContentLimit} content items in a space.",limitOne:"You can create 1 shared space with up to {spaceMemberLimit} members and {spaceContentLimit} content items in the space.",limitUnlimited:"You can create an unlimited number of shared spaces with up to {spaceMemberLimit} members and {spaceContentLimit} content items in a space.",name:"Shared Spaces",unlimited:"You can create an unlimited number of shared spaces with up to {memberMax} members and have up to {contentMax} content items in a space."},sso:{forOrgAccounts:"for organization accounts",info:"With an organization account you can set up SSO via SAML and enable your members to log in to Cloud via your authentication system.",infoLabel:"More info about SSO",member:"If you are a member of an organization account with SSO enabled, you may be able to log in via SSO.",name:"SSO"},students:{infoLabel:"More info about students",name:"Students"}},finePrint:"Fine Print:",licenses:{"cloud-free":"Cloud Free","cloud-student":"Cloud Student"},limits:{hours:{whatCounts:"What counts towards your compute hours?",yourWorkspace:'Projects you work on in "Your Workspace"',ownedSpace:"Projects you, or others, work on in your shared spaces",doesNotCount:"What does not count towards your compute hours?",otherSpaces:"Projects you work on in others' shared spaces",overages:"More than {count} compute hours in the month are billed at {cost} per additional compute hour."}},members:{basic:"Basic Members",changeAnytime:"To begin - you can adjust at any time.",details:{orderRequest:{instructor:"For accounts paid in advance, reach out to our sales team to adjust the number of instructors during the lifetime of your purchase.",member:"For accounts paid in advance, reach out to our sales team to adjust the number of members during the lifetime of your purchase."},selfServe:{instructor:"You can adjust the number of instructors at any time for accounts billed monthly.",member:"You can adjust the number of members at any time for accounts billed monthly."}},faq:"See the FAQs below for more details.",howMany:"how many?",instructor:"Instructors:",member:"Members:"},newOrganizationName:"Your organization's name",noData:"Sorry, unable to retrieve pricing data at this time. Please try again later.",orderInfo:{additionalInfo:"Additional info / questions",creditCard:"Credit card",debitCard:"Debit card",instructions:"provide your order details.",minimumAmount:{alternative:"Consider a monthly subscription instead. There is no minimum purchase required, and a subscription provides more flexibility - you can add or remove students as needed based on your actual enrollment.",details:"We can only process single payment orders that exceed {minAmount}.",title:"Minimum Order Total"},monthCount:"Number of Months",paymentMethod:"Payment method",purchaseOrder:"Purchase order",startDate:"Start Date",title:"Order Info:",yourName:"Your name"},orgAccountExplainer:{existing:"We will create a <strong>new account</strong> with this name for your organization. To purchase a {planType} plan for an existing account, please select it from the list.",help:"Which is right for me?",unauthenticated:"We will create a <strong>new account</strong> with this name for your organization. To purchase a {planType} plan for an existing account, please <a href={loginURL}>log in</a>, and then select your account from the list.",you:'We will create a <strong>new account</strong> with this name for your organization. To instead purchase a {planType} plan for yourself, please select "you" from the list.'},pageTitle:"Plans",payment:{instructions:"enter your credit/debit card and billing address.",method:"Payments must be made by credit or debit card.",onFile:"on file.",overages:"Any overages are charged at the end of your monthly billing cycle, along with the subscription fee for the upcoming month.",title:"Payment:"},pleaseRead:"please read.",questions:'Questions? <a class="fontBold" href="https://posit.co/about/contact/?utm_content=posit_cloud" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Contact Us.</a>',reactivate:"Reactivate",students:{cost:"how to cover their costs?",instructor:{cost:"You pay for actual usage via metered billing",details1:"You can have an unlimited number of students.",details2:"There is no per student fee - but you pay a variable monthly bill based on actual usage. Your students sign up with the {freePlanLink} plan; when they work in your course spaces, they gain access to your advanced features and use your included compute hours. You are responsible for any charges resulting from additional compute hours used in your spaces.",details3:"Estimate your monthly bill",title:"Metered Billing"},"instructor-fee-per-student":{cost:"You pay a per student fee",details1:"You pay $5 per month per student. Your students sign up with the {freePlanLink} plan. When they work in your course spaces, they gain access to your advanced features - and neither you nor your students are charged for any compute hours used in your spaces.",details2:{monthlyBillingOption:"You can adjust the number of students at anytime for accounts billed monthly.",payUpfrontBillingOption:"For accounts paid in advance, you will have to reach out to our sales team to adjust the number of students during the lifetime of your purchase."},details3:"See the FAQs below for more details.",title:"Fee per Student"},"instructor-student-pay":{cost:"Each student pays",details1:"You can have an unlimited number of students.",details2:{student:"Each student must sign up for a paid subscription to access projects in your course spaces. Typically the {studentPlanLink} plan for {studentPrice} / month is the right plan for students."},details3:"When students work in your course spaces, they gain access to advanced features included in your Instructor plan - and neither you nor your students are charged for any compute hours used in your spaces.",title:"Students Pay"},count:"Number of students",title:"Students:"},whoIsThisFor:"who is this for?",you:"You",yourOrganization:"Your organization / team",free:{name:"Cloud Free",shortTitle:"Free",signUp:"Sign Up for Cloud Free",switch:"Switch to Cloud Free",summary:"If you make limited, occasional use of Posit Cloud, have access to an organization account, or just want to explore Cloud to see if it's right for you, our Cloud Free plan is all you need.",features:{title:"Cloud Free Features",beta:{info:"On the Free plan, you cannot request early access to Beta features."},hours:{limit:"The Cloud Free plan has a cap each month of 25 compute hours. Once you reach the cap, you can no longer open or create projects during your current month."},sso:{info:"On the Free plan, you cannot set up SSO."}}},plus:{name:"Cloud Plus",shortTitle:"Plus"},premium:{name:"Cloud Premium",shortTitle:"Premium",variants:{list:"List price",academic:"Academic research",nonprofit:"Nonprofit",smallbiz:"Small business",smallbizdev:"Small business, developing country",mediumbiz:"Medium-sized business",mediumbizdev:"Medium-sized business, developing country"},academic:{title:"Academic Research"},nonprofit:{title:"Nonprofit"},smallbiz:{title:"Small Business"},smallbizdev:{title:"Small Business in a Developing Country"},mediumbiz:{title:"Medium Business"},mediumbizdev:{title:"Medium Business in a Developing Country"}},basic:{name:"Cloud Basic",orgAvailability:"The Cloud Basic plan is available for both individuals and organizations / teams.",purchase:"Purchase Cloud Basic",shortTitle:"Basic",summary:"The Cloud Basic plan offers you an affordable and reliable way to get started with professional data science tools and capabilities in the cloud.",switch:"Switch to Cloud Basic",features:{sso:{info:"On the Basic plan, you cannot set up SSO."},title:"Cloud Basic Features"}},standard:{name:"Cloud Standard",orgAvailability:"The Cloud Standard plan is available for both individuals and organizations / teams.",purchase:"Purchase Cloud Standard",shortTitle:"Standard",summary:"The Cloud Standard plan provides enhanced features and computing power to manage your more advanced data analysis and publishing workflows.",switch:"Switch to Cloud Standard",features:{title:"Cloud Standard Features"}},instructor:{academic:{requirements:"You are eligible if you are teaching at an accredited institution that meets one of the following qualifications:"},discount:{title:"Requirements:"},name:"Cloud Instructor",shortTitle:"Instructor: Metered Billing",orgAvailability:"The Cloud Instructor plan is available for both individuals and organizations / teams.",purchase:"Purchase Cloud Instructor",summary:"Cloud Instructor provides advanced features to instructors and organizations at a deep discount - and we offer three convenient ways to cover student costs to fit your budgeting requirements.",switch:"Switch to Cloud Instructor",features:{students:{limit:"You can have up to {studentMax} students in your account.",limitUnlimited:"Add virtually any number of students to your course spaces."},title:"Cloud Instructor Features"},eligibility:{accredited:{higherEd:"a public or private university or college (including community, junior or vocational college) that grants degrees requiring not less than the equivalent of two years of full-time study",k12:"a public or private primary or secondary school providing full-time instruction for grades K–12",hospital:"a hospital that is wholly owned and operated by an education institution",lab:"a higher-education research laboratory that is a public institution, teaches students, and can provide evidence of relationships with universities"}}},"instructor-fee-per-student":{name:"Cloud Instructor: Fee Per Student",orgAvailability:"The Cloud Instructor plan is available for both individuals and organizations / teams.",shortTitle:"Instructor: Fee Per Student"},"instructor-student-pay":{name:"Cloud Instructor: Students Pay",orgAvailability:"The Cloud Instructor plan is available for both individuals and organizations / teams.",shortTitle:"Instructor: Students Pay"},student:{academic:{requirements:"You are eligible if you are a student at an accredited institution that meets one of the following qualifications:"},discount:{title:"Requirements:"},name:"Cloud Student",purchase:"Purchase Cloud Student",shortTitle:"Student",summary:"The Cloud Student plan provides the features of our Cloud Free plan, but with additional time per month. You get 75 compute hours included per month, and can use additional hours as needed for 10¢ per compute hour.",switch:"Switch to Cloud Student",features:{title:"Cloud Student Features"}},custom:{name:"Cloud Custom",shortTitle:"Custom"}},comparePlans:{betaAccess:"Beta Features Access",bigMonthlyPrice:'<span class="bigPrice">{price}</span> / month',cloud:"Cloud",concurrentProjects:"Concurrent Projects",connections:"Data Connections",cpu:"Max CPU",education:{qualifications:"For qualifying educators and students"},execution:"Max Execution",hours:"Compute Hours",hoursDetail:"included per month<br />additional @ {cost} per hour",learnMore:"Learn more",monthlyPrice:"{price} / month",na:"NA",onlineSupport:"Online Support",orgAvailability:{header:"Also available for organizations / teams",property:"for organizations / teams"},price:"Price",projects:"Projects",ram:"Max RAM",sharedSpaces:"Shared Spaces",spaceLimits:"(with member & project limits)",sso:"SSO via SAML",te